# Frontend Architecture

## Folder structure

```
frontend/src/
  features/
    core/                    # app shell, auth gate, shared layout only
    feature_auth/
      LoginPage.tsx
      services/              # AuthService, etc.
    feature_issues/
      IssuesPage.tsx
      hooks/                 # useIssues, etc.
      components/            # feature-only UI
    feature_chat/
      ChatPage.tsx
      components/
      hooks/
    feature_<name>/
      <Page>.tsx
      hooks/
      components/
      services/
  widgets/                   # truly shared, reusable across features only
  services/                  # cross-cutting infra only (e.g. HttpService)
  routes/
    MainRoutes.tsx
  cms/
    routes/CmsRoutes.tsx
```

## Feature colocation (required)

- Put **hooks, components, and services with the feature that uses them**
- Example: `useIssues` lives in `features/feature_issues/hooks/`, not `src/hooks/`
- Do **not** create global `src/hooks/` for feature logic
- `widgets/` and `src/services/` are only for code reused by **multiple** features
- If unsure, default to the feature folder

## Features

- New domains go in `features/feature_<name>/`
- `features/core` holds shell/layout/auth gate only
- Feature folders own their pages + local hooks/components/services

## Widgets

- Prefer small reusable widgets in `widgets/` only when shared across features
- Feature-specific UI stays under that feature’s `components/`

## Data & forms

- Load server data with **TanStack Query** (`useQuery` / `useMutation`)
- Forms with **React Hook Form**
- Feature hooks encapsulate fetch logic

## HTTP

- All API calls go through `HttpService` (`get`, `post`, `put`, `patch`, `delete`)
- Do not call `fetch`/`axios` directly from page components

## Routing

- Register app routes only in `routes/MainRoutes.tsx`
- Register CMS/admin routes only in `cms/routes/CmsRoutes.tsx`
